    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA190-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu piṉṉiṉṟa talaimakaṉ āṟṟāṉāy (EN, ER, ET: āki; EV: ākiya) neñciṟkuc colliyatu. 2. allakuṟippaṭṭu mīḷvāṉ neñciṟkuc colliyatūumām.
            3. iṭaiccurattuc (ET: iṭaiccurattiṉkaṇ) ceṉṟu talaimakaḷ nalam uḷḷi mīḷal uṟṟa neñciṉaik kaḻaṟiyatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what HE who stood behind [her] said to [his] heart, being one who could not bear it. 2. It is also what the one who returned after having been led astray by a [wrong] sign said to [his] heart. 3. It is also how he reproaches the heart that suffers [from the wish] to go back when remembering HER beauty after having gone right into the desert.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA190">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            nōviṉi vāḻiya neñcē mēvā</l>
<l>            rāraraṇ kaṭanta māri vaṇmakiḻt</l>
<l>            titalai yeḵkiṟ cēntaṉ ṟantai</l>
<l>            tēṅkamaḻ viritā riyaṟē raḻici</l>
<l>            vaṇṭumūcu neyta ṉelliṭai malaru </l>
<l>            mariyalaṅ kaḻaṉi yārkkāṭ ṭaṉṉa</l>
<l>            kāmar paṇaittō ṇalamvī ṟeytiya</l>
<l>            valaimāṉ maḻaikkaṭ kuṟumakaḷ</l>
<l>            ciṉmoḻit tuvarvāy nakaikkumakiḻn tōyē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>        Ache now – may you live, heart –</l>
<l>        you who delighted in the smile of the coral mouth with few words</l>
<l rend="indent">            of the little woman with rain eyes, [as] a deer in the net,</l>
<l rend="indent">            who has reached distinction in the goodness of [her] desirable</l>
<l rend="indent4">                 bamboo shoulder,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            as Ārkāṭu with [its] toddy<note place="foot">T.V.G. wants to understand <term xml:lang="ta">ariyal</term>, once more against the dictionaries, as honey here, taking <term xml:lang="ta">kaḻaṉi</term> as the paddy fields which are so much interspersed with waterlilies that lots of honey is made there.</note> fields,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            where bee-swarmed blue waterlilies are blossoming between the paddy,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            of Aḻici with swift chariots [and] honey-scented broad garlands,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            father of Cēntaṉ with a [red-]dotted<note place="foot">T.V.G. points out, rather plausibly, that the beauty spots of a lance consist of enemy blood.</note> lance,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            a delight<note place="foot">T.V.G. wants to understand <term xml:lang="ta">makiḻ</term> as "toddy" here, but then the context would be completely elliptical: is he himself intoxicated by toddy (and frequently at that), does he give toddy away?</note>, generous [as] the clouds, who surmounted</l>
<l rend="indent3">            the difficult fortress of [his] foes.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
